{"id": 243341950, "title": "TLC STAFF DOWN TOOLS OVER UNPAID SALARIES", "text": "One of the sources close to the matter said due to the financial challenges that have been faced by the institution, they were informed by management that it was becoming more and more difficult to fund operations, as well as pay their salaries. The source said last month they managed to get their salaries, but were informed by management that things were not looking good. \u201cThis month, management informed us that they could not pay our salaries, hence the decision to down tools,\u201d said the source. Adding, the source said they were banking their hopes on government to come and bail the TLC out, as it was evident that their services were needed in the country.", "summary": "MBABANE &ndash; Yesterday employees&nbsp; of&nbsp; TLC downed tools over unpaid salaries.\nIn light of the ongoing financial challenges faced by The Luke Commission (TLC), their employees", "url": "http://www.times.co.sz/sports/145829-tlc-staff-down-tools-over-unpaid-salaries.html", "image": null, "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 05:47:00", "author": "The Luke Commission", "authors": ["The Luke Commission"], "language": "en", "source_country": "sz", "sentiment": -0.779}